<div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 p-3 md:p-6 transition-colors duration-300"
     data-controller="text-toggle font-controls"
     data-text-toggle-target="content"
     data-font-controls-target="content">

  <%= render 'shared/page_header', pagina: @pagina %>

  <div class="space-y-6">

    <!-- Introduzione goniometro -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-200">
        <p>Per misurare l'ampiezza degli angoli usiamo il <span class="font-bold">goniometro</span>, uno strumento suddiviso in 180° (angolo piatto) o in 360° (angolo giro).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex justify-center">
        <%= image_tag "nvi4_mat/p113/p113_01.jpg", class: "max-w-full h-auto dark:bg-white dark:rounded-lg dark:p-2", alt: "Goniometri 180° e 360°" %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Come usare il goniometro -->
    <div class="p-4 bg-custom-blue dark:bg-cyan-900 rounded-2xl">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-200">
            <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-<%= @pagina.base_color %>-500 text-white font-bold mr-2">1</span>
            Fai coincidere il centro del goniometro con il vertice dell'angolo e la linea che passa per lo 0 con un lato dell'angolo.
          </p>
          <div class="flex justify-center">
            <%= image_tag "nvi4_mat/p113/p113_02.jpg", class: "max-w-full h-auto dark:bg-white dark:rounded-lg dark:p-2", alt: "Goniometro posizionato" %>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-200">
            <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-<%= @pagina.base_color %>-500 text-white font-bold mr-2">2</span>
            Leggi sul goniometro i gradi in corrispondenza dell'altro lato dell'angolo.
          </p>
          <div class="flex justify-center">
            <%= image_tag "nvi4_mat/p113/p113_03.jpg", class: "max-w-full h-auto dark:bg-white dark:rounded-lg dark:p-2", alt: "Lettura goniometro 50°" %>
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-200 text-center font-bold">In questo caso l'angolo misura 50°.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Classificazione angoli -->
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-200">
        <span class="text-<%= @pagina.base_color %>-500">&#9654;</span> Conoscere l'ampiezza degli angoli è utile per identificarli e <span class="font-bold">classificarli</span>.
      </p>

      <div class="p-4 md:p-6 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-2xl border-3 border-blue-800 dark:border-blue-600">
        <!-- Prima riga: retto, acuto, ottuso -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-6">
          <div class="text-center space-y-2">
            <%= image_tag "nvi4_mat/p113/p113_04.jpg", class: "max-w-full h-auto mx-auto dark:bg-white dark:rounded-lg dark:p-2", alt: "Angolo retto" %>
            <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-200">90°: <span class="font-bold">angolo retto</span></p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center space-y-2">
            <%= image_tag "nvi4_mat/p113/p113_05.jpg", class: "max-w-full h-auto mx-auto dark:bg-white dark:rounded-lg dark:p-2", alt: "Angolo acuto" %>
            <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-200">minore di 90°: <span class="font-bold">angolo acuto</span></p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center space-y-2">
            <%= image_tag "nvi4_mat/p113/p113_06.jpg", class: "max-w-full h-auto mx-auto dark:bg-white dark:rounded-lg dark:p-2", alt: "Angolo ottuso" %>
            <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-200">maggiore di 90°: <span class="font-bold">angolo ottuso</span></p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Seconda riga: piatto, giro, nullo + nota -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
          <div class="text-center space-y-2">
            <%= image_tag "nvi4_mat/p113/p113_07.jpg", class: "max-w-full h-auto mx-auto dark:bg-white dark:rounded-lg dark:p-2", alt: "Angolo piatto" %>
            <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-200">180°: <span class="font-bold">angolo piatto</span></p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">(2 volte angolo retto)</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center space-y-2">
            <%= image_tag "nvi4_mat/p113/p113_08.jpg", class: "max-w-full h-auto mx-auto dark:bg-white dark:rounded-lg dark:p-2", alt: "Angolo giro" %>
            <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-200">360°: <span class="font-bold">angolo giro</span></p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">(4 volte angolo retto)</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center space-y-2">
            <%= image_tag "nvi4_mat/p113/p113_09.jpg", class: "max-w-full h-auto mx-auto dark:bg-white dark:rounded-lg dark:p-2", alt: "Angolo nullo" %>
            <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-200">0°: <span class="font-bold">angolo nullo</span></p>
          </div>
          <div class="self-center text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-200">
            <p>Avrai notato che si usa come riferimento l'angolo retto (90°), cioè l'angolo convesso formato da due semirette perpendicolari.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <%= render 'shared/quaderno_link', pagine: [236, 237] %>

    <%= render 'shared/exercise_controls' %>
  </div>
</div>
